    "text": "MISSOULA, Mont. â€” Ski resorts in Montana are back open after the weekend's Arctic temperatures. Turner Mountain opens for the season today. Blacktail Mountain is now open. Visitors are on packed powder and machine groomed runs with the Olympic and Thunderhead lifts in operation. Maverick Mountain is open today as well. Whitefish Mountain Resort has gotten chairs 2,3, 6 and 9 running. Night skiing and children's programs are canceled. Snowbowl says it's open today, with a delayed start for the upper mountain. Red Lodge Mountain is open. It got the Triple Chair, The Stache Express, and other lifts running. Great Divide near Marysville is open with at least six inches of new snow in the past several days. Showdown outside Neihart has the Triple Chair, Caboose and Learning Conveyor running, with 12 new inches recently. Lost Trail will have a delayed opening at 11 a.m. today and it's offering discounted lift tickets. Discovery has 25 percent of its terrain open, and now running the Anaconda lift. Big Sky reports at least 14 inches of new snow in the last week. Bridger Bowl reports a delayed opening at 10 a.m. today.",
